README for lua_omni.vim (Version 0.17) / May 20 2011

    * INSTALATION
    * RELEASE NOTES 
    * FILES

lua_omni.vim implements omni completion function for Lua. It works by scanning
the _G table for names and parsing Vim buffers. File(s) with predefined Lua
completions can be used too. There are some abbreviations and Lua function
list option added as well.

=======================================================================================
  INSTALLATION
=======================================================================================

Just extract and copy files from lua_omni.zip into local .vim/ftplugin and
.vim/doc directories. Then execute in Vim:
    :helptags ~/.vim/doc

To get a help type:
    :help lua_omni

Beware! Vim 7.3 is needed with enabled Lua support.


=======================================================================================
  RELEASE NOTES 
=======================================================================================

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  RELEASE NOTES FOR VERSION 0.17
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    + added folding for Lua code by foldexpr function


=======================================================================================
  FILES
=======================================================================================

README.lua_omni                 This file.
ftplugin/lua_omni.vim           A filetype plugin. Define functions, shortcuts
                                and abbreviations.
ftplugin/lua_omni.lua           A file with Lua functions. Used by
                                lua_omni.vim.
doc/lua_omni.txt                Vim help file with lua_omni documentation.
